article.headline: St. Francis, Pa., 70, Liberty 56
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. (AP) -- Marquis Ford scored 16 points and hit two 3-pointers during a second-half run to lead St. Francis, Pa., to a 70-56 win over Liberty on Saturday night. With the win, the Red Flash (4-5) matched their victory total of last season and snapped Liberty's six-game winning streak. Devin Sweetney scored all 14 of his points in the second half, and J.R. Enright also finished with 14 for St. Francis. Cale Nelson added 10 points. Dwight Brewington, a transfer from Providence playing his first game with the Flames, scored a team-best 16 points. Anthony Smith and Larry Blair each scored 11 for Liberty (6-2). The teams were tied at 24-all at the break before Ford made back-to-back 3-pointers to start a 15-6 run. Ford helped finish off the outburst by feeding Nelson for a 3-pointer on a fast break to give St. Francis a 51-39 lead with 5:57 left.
